TASK 4 EMAIL ETIQUETTE

Poor digital communication can easily lead to misunderstandings in 
everyday situations. For example, one of my classmates once messaged 
our group chat late at night saying, “Assignment postponed.” The 
message was very short and had no details. Some students assumed 
that the deadline had officially been extended by the teacher, while 
others thought it was just a rumor. Because of this confusion, a few 
students did not complete their work on time. The next day, it turned 
out that the assignment had not been postponed at all—the student had 
only meant that he was planning to submit it late.
This misunderstanding happened because the message was unclear and 
lacked proper context. It could have been avoided if the student had 
written a complete and clear message, such as explaining that it was 
only his personal plan and not an official update. In digital 
communication, especially in group chats or emails, clarity is very 
important. Messages should include enough details so that others 
understand the exact meaning. Using proper sentences, context, and tone 
helps prevent confusion and ensures that information is communicated 
correctly.


TASK 5 CYBERCRIME
While researching cybercrime, I was surprised by how easily people fall 
victim to simple scams like UPI fraud. Many victims are not careless but 
simply unaware of how these systems work. I realized that even a small 
mistake, like scanning a QR code or sharing an OTP, can lead to financial 
loss within seconds.
One habit I will personally change is being more cautious while dealing 
with unknown messages, calls, or links. I will always verify before taking 
any action, especially in financial matters. I will also make sure to 
educate my friends and family about basic online safety rules. Being aware 
and alert is the best way to stay safe in the digital world.


